reated": 1775205668992, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 32, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": [{"width": 1206, "heightRatio": 112, "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HE83k0mWcAAE8Nt.jpg", "height": 1358}], "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 335, "created": 1775187481000, "id": "2039910265064419717", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1892661097175343105/-zjS7BtL_normal.jpg", "displayName": "FBI Director Kash Patel", "username": "FBIDirectorKash"}, "content": "Led by @realDonaldTrump and @VP\u2019s Task Force, this FBI will be working 24/7 with our partners across the country to root out fraud and eliminate the criminal networks who take advantage of taxpayers", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 2702}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZCyzeAG", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 14, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8533054, "raw_content": "Please help me tax those who tolerate the fraud that is bankrupting this nation. I just drafted this bill with the help of AI. It needs improvement, but it would punish the fraudsters, help pay down our national debt, and destroy the lives of the liberal scum that are defrauding all of us. This bill has not been introduced into Congress yet.\n\nA BILL\n\nTo amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to impose a geographically-adjusted federal tax reflecting public fraud losses.\n\nSECTION 1. SHORT TITLE.\nThis Act may be cited as the \u201cFederal Fiscal Integrity Act.\u201d\n\nSEC. 2. IMPOSITION OF GEOGRAPHIC FRAUD ADJUSTMENT TAX.\n(a) In General.\u2014Chapter 1 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 is amended by adding at the end the following:\n\u201cSec. 59B. Geographic Fraud Adjustment Tax.\n\n(b) Imposition of Tax.\u2014\nIn the case of any applicable individual, there is hereby imposed for each taxable year a tax equal to the sum of\u2014\n(1) the State fraud adjustment amount; and  \n(2) the county fraud adjustment amount.\n\n(c) Applicable Individual.\u2014\nThe term \u2018applicable individual\u2019 means any individual who maintains a principal residence within the United States during the taxable year.\n\n(d) State Fraud Adjustment Amount.\u2014\nThe State fraud adjustment amount shall be equal to the per-capita amount of validated public fraud losses attributable to the State of residence of the taxpayer over the preceding 10 taxable years.\n\n(e) County Fraud Adjustment Amount.\u2014\nThe county fraud adjustment amount shall be equal to the per-capita amount of validated public fraud losses attributable to the county (or equivalent jurisdiction) of residence of the taxpayer over the preceding 10 taxable years.\n\n(f) Determination of Fraud Losses.\u2014\nFor purposes of this section, \u2018validated public fraud losses\u2019 means aggregate monetary losses identified through\u2014\n(1) reports of Inspectors General;  \n(2) audits and reports of the Government Accountability Office; and  \n(3) agency determinations of improper payments or fraud, as defined by the Secretary.\n\n(g) Per-Capita Calculation.\u2014\nPer-capita amounts shall be determined by dividing total validated public fraud losses by the adult population of the relevant jurisdiction, as determined by the Secretary.\n\n(h) Collection.\u2014\nThe tax imposed under this section shall be assessed and collected in the same manner as taxes under this title.\n\n(i) Treatment.\u2014\nThe tax imposed under this section shall be treated as a tax for all purposes of this title.\n\n(j) Regulations.\u2014\nThe Secretary shall prescribe such regulations as are necessary to carry out this section, including rules for geographic attribution.\u201d", "author": "LiberalsAreMental", "created": 1775212630439, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Support the \"Federal Fiscal Integrity Act\" to tax those who tolerate fraud.", "last_comment_created": 1775212630438, "content": "<p>Please help me tax those who tolerate the fraud that is bankrupting this nation. I just drafted this bill with the help of AI. It needs improvement, but it would punish the fraudsters, help pay down our national debt, and destroy the lives of the liberal scum that are defrauding all of us. This bill has not been introduced into Congress yet.</p>\n<p>A BILL</p>\n<p>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to impose a geographically-adjusted federal tax reflecting public fraud losses.</p>\n<p>SECTION 1. SHORT TITLE.\nThis Act may be cited as the \u201cFederal Fiscal Integrity Act.\u201d</p>\n<p>SEC. 2. IMPOSITION OF GEOGRAPHIC FRAUD ADJUSTMENT TAX.\n(a) In General.\u2014Chapter 1 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 is amended by adding at the end the following:\n\u201cSec. 59B. Geographic Fraud Adjustment Tax.</p>\n<p>(b) Imposition of Tax.\u2014\nIn the case of any applicable individual, there is hereby imposed for each taxable year a tax equal to the sum of\u2014\n(1) the State fraud adjustment amount; and<br />\n(2) the county fraud adjustment amount.</p>\n<p>(c) Applicable Individual.\u2014\nThe term \u2018applicable individual\u2019 means any individual who maintains a principal residence within the United States during the taxable year.</p>\n<p>(d) State Fraud Adjustment Amount.\u2014\nThe State fraud adjustment amount shall be equal to the per-capita amount of validated public fraud losses attributable to the State of residence of the taxpayer over the preceding 10 taxable years.</p>\n<p>(e) County Fraud Adjustment Amount.\u2014\nThe county fraud adjustment amount shall be equal to the per-capita amount of validated public fraud losses attributable to the county (or equivalent jurisdiction) of residence of the taxpayer over the preceding 10 taxable years.</p>\n<p>(f) Determination of Fraud Losses.\u2014\nFor purposes of this section, \u2018validated public fraud losses\u2019 means aggregate monetary losses identified through\u2014\n(1) reports of Inspectors General;<br />\n(2) audits and reports of the Government Accountability Office; and<br />\n(3) agency determinations of improper payments or fraud, as defined by the Secretary.</p>\n<p>(g) Per-Capita Calculation.\u2014\nPer-capita amounts shall be determined by dividing total validated public fraud losses by the adult population of the relevant jurisdiction, as determined by the Secretary.</p>\n<p>(h) Collection.\u2014\nThe tax imposed under this section shall be assessed and collected in the same manner as taxes under this title.</p>\n<p>(i) Treatment.\u2014\nThe tax imposed under this section shall be treated as a tax for all purposes of this title.</p>\n<p>(j) Regulations.\u2014\nThe Secretary shall prescribe such regulations as are necessary to carry out this section, including rules for geographic attribution.\u201d</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 14, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}], "status": true}